Art. 123 - In addition to the domains intended to the organic laws by the Constitution, the 
Parliament legislates through organic laws in the following fields: 
- organization and functioning of public powers; 
- electoral regulation; 
- the law pertaining to political parties;

- the law pertaining to political parties; 
